$interpreted: Elio: ...Just looking at the results of this experiment,
Elio: being bewitched appears similar to being infected by a monster. It’s almost the same, except...
Li Hwa: What? Are you stuck?
Elio: Well, if I want to prove it, I’ll have to find a concrete similarity between a bewitcher and a monster.
Elio: They’re obviously completely different on the outside, not to mention that current knowledge on monsters is rather limited...
Li Hwa: You don’t know where to begin?
Elio: Right...
Tica: Eh? I think it worked!
Li Hwa: Tica, did you alchemize this?

Elio: It’s so sparkly, I’ve never seen this before.
Is this soul energy?
Tica: I don’t know, really, I was just alchemizing randomly. But this is totally different from any soul energy I’ve ever learned about.
Elio: What are you using as a source? Bewitcher hair? And what order of soul energy is this?
Tica: Um...
Tica: So it seems like bewitcher soul energy is very similar to a monster's...
Tica: I got curious because of how the bottom part of the strand here sparkles.
Elio: It's like a monster's, but at the same time it's different.
Li Hwa: ...Hold on a second.
Li Hwa: Just as I thought... this is 'Qi'.
Elio: Qi...? You mean, the kind of Qi only beasts have?
Li Hwa: Yes, and you said you’ve never seen this kind of energy before? Maybe that explains why only beasts can turn into bewitchers.
Tica: You're right! Maybe the reason they change in a way similar to monsters has something to do with this sparkly bit!
Li Hwa: This could be a breakthrough! Let’s keep experimenting with this soul energy!
Tica: Okay!!
Elio: Let's do it!
Scared Bewitcher: We’ve got a problem!!
Scared Bewitcher: Li Hwa, they’re at Lake Illumina!! B-Bull Tribe soldiers!!
Tica: Soldiers!?
Scared Bewitcher: Just now, in the middle of the night. I was just taking a walk, minding my own business...
Scared Bewitcher: They stopped some of us that couldn't escape in time!
Elio: Have they found us?
Li Hwa: And it has to be now, while Soohyeon isn’t here...
Li Hwa: Very well, bring us over, let us see for ourselves!
Bull Contestant: Can’t believe that maggot was telling the truth!
Bull Contestant: Alright, get ‘em! Kill ‘em all, I don’t want anyone left alive!
Bull Soldier: Yes, sir!
Elio: Stop!!
Threatened Bewitcher: He-Help me!
Li Hwa: Stop this! We've done nothing wrong!
Bull Contestant: Nothing wrong!? You’re the one who’s been keeping them here, right? Now you have the gall to say you’ve done nothing wrong!?
Tica: Miss Li Hwa!
Bull Contestant: Harboring so many bewitchers... Do you realize how many innocent people you’ve gotten killed!?

Bull Contestant: What did they do!? Why did they deserve to die!?
Huh!? Tell me!!
Li Hwa: Ah...
Scared Bewitcher: Ah, it’s... it’s all my fault! Please, don’t blame Li Hwa!

Bull Contestant: Don’t you try and touch me!!
You’re all gonna die anyway, might as well be right now!
Elio: Leave him alone!!
Tica: Be careful, Elio!!
Tica: ...Ah...
Elio: You... how...?

Bull Contestant: Another human!? 
Why’re you all coming out of the woodwork!?
Sione: ......

Sione: This soldier is strong, maybe too strong for me to handle alone.
Can you stand?
Elio: What are you... doing here...?
Sione: Queen Angelia ordered me to watch over you.

Elio: Watch over me...?
Queen Angelia is... keeping tabs on me?
Sione: There are only two kinds of people the Queen keeps tabs on. Enemies, and those she wants to protect. You’re the latter.
Elio: She's... protecting me?
Sione: You’re not just Theodore’s son...You’re also Queen Angelia’s cousin, her blood relative.
Elio: ...You’re saying, Queen Angelia, she's my...!?
Sione: —Watch out!
Bull Contestant: You...
Bull Soldier: Sir, they might be on a diplomatic mission from the Kingdom of the Sun... If we injure them, we could be in trouble.
Bull Contestant: I’m sick of all these diplomats! The Alliance doesn’t need them!
Bull Contestant: I don’t care where they’re from, just kill ‘em!!
Sione: Now, run!!
Li Hwa: Bring everyone back to Pearl Manor!

Tica: Ah, that wound looks like it hurts!
Just hold on a little longer~
Elio: What is this...?
Li Hwa: I made this a long, long time ago with the madame of Seamoon Manor. We were inspired by the three sect walls, so we made this in their likeness.
Li Hwa: It’s meant for use in case of emergencies... I’ve actually never used it before.
Li Hwa: The current is incredibly strong, and dangerous.
Li Hwa: Unless they were amazing swimmers, with immense physical strength, they'd never make it through.
Elio: ...But, we’re trapped here in the manor, right? And we can’t leave?
Li Hwa: ...That's right.
Sione: ...So now it’s just a waiting game? There’s no saying we’re in a better position than they are...
Li Hwa: That's right, unless we get outside help.
Li Hwa: And yet, a manor full of bewitchers, enemies of the Alliance... Who would ever come help us?
